title.#text: Side-tracked: unique evidence for passage of foetuses through the lateral vaginal canals in a dasyurid marsupial,

author.details: Department of Ecology, Environment and Evolution, La Trobe University, Melbourne, Vic. 3086, Australia.

front.abstract: An abnormal female reproductive tract of the dasyurid marsupial Sminthopsis douglasi is described, which provides unequivocal evidence for parturition through the lateral vaginae of this female.
front.keywords: median vaginal cul-de-sac, parturition, pseudo-vaginal canal, ureter.
